messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full path
- /api/user/

All methods acceptable
- false

Methods acceptable (based on the code)
- HEAD: false
- POST: false
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: true
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation
- In main (hello.go) the router root group is created as v1 := r.Group("/api").
- UserRegister is called with v1.Group("/user"), so the effective prefix for the routes in UserRegister is /api + /user.
- Inside users/routers.go, UserRegister registers:
  - router.GET("/", UserRetrieve)
  - router.PUT("/", UserUpdate)
  These correspond to the full path /api/user/ (the group prefix plus the "/" path registered).
- No other HTTP methods (POST, DELETE, PATCH, HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, or a catchâ€‘all/Any) are registered for that specific route in the provided code. Per the instruction to base results on the code (not on framework behavior like implicit HEAD handling), only GET and PUT are considered acceptable.
- Note: the routes under /api/user/ are registered after v1.Use(users.AuthMiddleware(true)) in main, so those endpoints require the middleware, but that does not affect which HTTP methods are registered.
